TITLE: Implementing Redirect Callback in NextAuth.js
DESCRIPTION: Example of redirect callback implementation that validates and controls URL redirections. Ensures redirects only occur to trusted URLs within the same base URL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v3/configuration/callbacks.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
callbacks: {
  /**
   * @param  {string} url      URL provided as callback URL by the client
   * @param  {string} baseUrl  Default base URL of site (can be used as fallback)
   * @return {string}          URL the client will be redirect to
   */
  async redirect(url, baseUrl) {
    return url.startsWith(baseUrl)
      ? url
      : baseUrl
  }
}
```

