TITLE: Event Handling Overview for NextAuth.js
DESCRIPTION: Lists and describes all available events in NextAuth.js including signIn, signOut, createUser, updateUser, linkAccount, session, and error events. Each event provides specific data objects for auditing and debugging purposes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v3/configuration/events.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
### signIn
- `user` (from adapter or provider)
- `account` (from adapter or provider)
- `isNewUser` (new user status)

### signOut
- JWT or adapter session object

### createUser
- user object

### updateUser
- user object

### linkAccount
- `user`: adapter user object
- `providerAccount`: provider return object

### session
- `session`: adapter session object
- `jwt`: JWT token if enabled

### error
- error description object
```

