TITLE: Implementing Redirect Callback in NextAuth.js
DESCRIPTION: Default implementation of the redirect callback that handles URL validation and redirection. Ensures redirects are only allowed to URLs on the same domain by default.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/docs/blob/main/docs/configuration/callbacks.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
callbacks: {
  redirect({ url, baseUrl   }) {
    if (url.startsWith(baseUrl)) return url
    // Allows relative callback URLs
    else if (url.startsWith("/")) return new URL(url, baseUrl).toString()
    return baseUrl
  }
}
```

