TITLE: Creating a Custom User Model with TypeORM
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to extend the built-in User model from the TypeORM adapter in NextAuth.js, allowing for the addition of custom properties such as phoneNumber, while preserving existing properties. It requires NextAuth.js and TypeORM as dependencies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v3/tutorials/typeorm-custom-models.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import Adapters from "next-auth/adapters"

// Extend the built-in models using class inheritance
export default class User extends Adapters.TypeORM.Models.User.model {
  // You can extend the options in a model but you should not remove the base
  // properties or change the order of the built-in options on the constructor
  constructor(name, email, image, emailVerified) {
    super(name, email, image, emailVerified)
  }
}

export const UserSchema = {
  name: "User",
  target: User,
  columns: {
    ...Adapters.TypeORM.Models.User.schema.columns,
    // Adds a phoneNumber to the User schema
    phoneNumber: {
      type: "varchar",
      nullable: true,
    },
  },
}
```

