TITLE: Creating HTTPS Certificate for Local Development
DESCRIPTION: This bash command generates a self-signed SSL certificate for localhost, which is required for Bungie authentication in local development.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextauthjs/docs/blob/main/docs/providers/bungie.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
openssl req -x509 -out localhost.crt -keyout localhost.key \
  -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes -sha256 \
  -subj "/CN=localhost" -extensions EXT -config <( \
   printf "[dn]\nCN=localhost\n[req]\ndistinguished_name = dn\n[EXT]\nsubjectAltName=DNS:localhost\nkeyUsage=digitalSignature\nextendedKeyUsage=serverAuth")
```

